"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5223284-2024-01-24-caitlin-clark-team-usa-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NCAAW    USA Basketball will be seeking its eighth consecutive Olympic gold medal this summer with the first step coming at the Olympic qualifying tournament in Antwerp, Belgium, from Feb. 8-11.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9999999998753992, \"rank\": 1.2453957435074727e-10, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9878794711277236, \"rank\": 0.01226923845098014, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9428782144512109, \"rank\": 0.06057952265411795, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 12-player roster for that tournament will be the first approximation of the team that will defend the Americans' gold medal in Paris.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.3197570505636718e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Based on the 18 players who have been invited to the national team camp from Feb. 2-4 in Brooklyn, N.Y., the committee has a terrifically challenging task to select that final roster, a decision that will likely be further complicated by the current collegians - primarilyCaitlin Clark, but USABasketballveteransPaige BueckersandCameron Brinkcould also factor in here - who turn pro at the end of the 2023-24 season.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 438, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn_Nets\", \"score\": 0.9100468925360095, \"rank\": 0.09741075537696466, \"text\": \"Brooklyn\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn_Nets\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn_Nets\"}, {\"begin\": 599, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCD_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9998610878564174, \"rank\": 0.00013589088101063793, \"text\": \"collegians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCD_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCD_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final roster will ultimately make a statement about what the committee values: youth and the future or experience and proven success.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Basketball has generally balanced old and young on the international team so that the younger players can carry the torch and preserve the culture.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9999999998753992, \"rank\": 1.2453957435074727e-10, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Including - or not including -Clarkposes a unique dilemma with the wealth of options before the committee.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"18 athletes will be in camp with the \\ud83c\\uddfa\\ud83c\\uddf8#USABWNTFeb.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2-4 in prep for the#FIBAOQTin \\ud83c\\udde7\\ud83c\\uddea Antwerp.\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9878794711277236, \"rank\": 0.01226923845098014, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Antwerp_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- USA Basketball (@usabasketball)January 23, 2024    On the opposite end of the spectrum fromClarkisDiana Taurasi, one of eight Olympians from Tokyo in 2021 who is back in the national team pool.\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1372, \"end\": 1379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.412628853046436e-65, \"text\": \"Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taurasi is seeking to become the first basketball player of either gender to compete in sixOlympics.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She would also be the oldest basketball Olympian ever and the third American woman of any sport to participate in six games.\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basketball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.169173615464579e-21, \"text\": \"basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 1